description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of consultant urological surgeon with an interest in bladder cancer. The position attracts a total of 10 PAs and includes on call and clinical commitments at the St George&#39;s University Hospitals NHS Trust sites and sessions at Epsom and St Helier Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St George&#39;s University Hospitals NHS Trust is a joint specialist urological cancer centre with the Royal Marsden Hospital and is the major surgical centre in South West London for bladder cancer. We perform robotic cystectomy and provide a specialist service for high risk non muscle invasive bladder cancer, with a particular interest in BCG failure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Urology has 14 Consultant Urological Surgeons, supported by a dedicated team of Clinical Nurse Specialists. St. George’s Hospital is one of the largest teaching hospitals in the UK, closely integrated to St George&#39;s Medical School, part of the University of London. We are a joint cancer centre with the Royal Marsden Hospital and one of the key providers of secondary and tertiary services in South West London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job description is awaiting final sign off from the Royal College of Surgeons, any amendments will be sent to potential candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBenjamin AyresJob titleConsultant Urologist and clinical leadEmail addressbenjamin.ayres@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Mr. Benjamin Ayres via email should you wish to discuss this post further.&lt;/p&gt;
